{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"b313bd1f-c567-4181-8da6-92ef185beb0d","content":"The issue is the **F# file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types from files listed *above* them. Currently `Services.fs` is listed before `Domain.fs`, but `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_M8OQ2O0PLQ7nqKp4MouGM6","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-b6a7b7d11ad24ad786ca7f9afc9f68ea/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <ItemGroup>\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Program.fs\" />\n  </ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-b6a7b7d11ad24ad786ca7f9afc9f68ea/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"8c8ff06d-31c3-402a-9f78-0d3ec6dd5141","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters - files can only reference types/modules defined in files that appear *before* them in the compilation order. \n\nLooking at the `.fsproj`:\n1. `Services.fs` is listed first\n2. `Domain.fs` is listed second\n3. `Program.fs` is listed third\n\nBut `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs` (it opens `BrokenOrder.Domain`), so `Domain.fs` must come before `Services.fs`. And `Program.fs` depends on both, so it should come last.\n\nThe correct order should be:\n\n\n1. `Domain.fs`\n2. `Services.fs`\n3. `Program.fs`","outputTokens":465,"requestId":"0423:B3321:C43C9E:E23DDA:69F2A77B"},"id":"99fd1d98-98e5-43aa-9ffd-29edd31de841","timestamp":"2026-04-30T00:51:17.937Z","parentId":"e2d7deb9-249f-4d73-afaa-6c8190f1bc36"}
